# ARC1X Game Folder — Comprehensive Build Plan

## Current State Analysis

The project has:

- __`docker-game/`__ — A Docker-focused game container with 32 files (server, clients, engine modules, infra configs, HTML clients)
- __4,816+ ARC1X system files__ in the root directory (Quantum, Biological, Reality, Temporal, Void, ArchMode, Phase systems)
- __`ARC1X_SYSTEM_INTEGRATION_NEXUS.cjs`__ — Central integration hub (4,272+ systems registered)
- __`ARC1X_AUXILIARY_SYSTEMS_LAUNCHER.js`__ — Module loader with lazy loading for 3,500+ systems
- __`Arc1x-Folders-Base/docker-game-build/`__ — A sibling directory with `ARC1X_GAME_COMPLETE.cjs` (reference complete game)
- __Core game modules__ already in `docker-game/`: drone system, graphics engine, asset system, pipeline, compile, unified engine, asset controls, drone pilot

The `docker-game/` folder is currently mixed-purpose (Docker infra + game code). The user wants a __dedicated game scripts folder__ that organizes __all__ components into a proper modular game build with nexus integration, on par with current game releases.

